# Purpose

Verify the derive(Signature) macro generates syntactically correct code before integrating with ChatAdapter.

## Why This Matters

The derive macro is complex. Catching issues early (before integration) is much faster than debugging through the full stack.

## Test Approach

```rust
// In crates/dsrs-macros/tests/signature_derive.rs

#[derive(Signature)]
/// Test instruction
struct TestSig {
    #[input]
    question: String,

    #[output]
    answer: String,
}

#[test]
fn test_generates_input_struct() {
    // TestSigInput should exist and have correct fields
    let input = TestSigInput { question: "test".into() };
    assert_eq!(input.question, "test");
}

#[test]
fn test_generates_signature_impl() {
    // Signature trait should be implemented
    assert_eq!(<TestSig as Signature>::instruction(), "Test instruction");
    assert_eq!(<TestSig as Signature>::input_fields().len(), 1);
    assert_eq!(<TestSig as Signature>::output_fields().len(), 1);
}

#[test]
fn test_from_parts_into_parts() {
    let input = TestSigInput { question: "q".into() };
    let output = __TestSigOutput { answer: "a".into() };

    let full = TestSig::from_parts(input.clone(), output);
    assert_eq!(full.question, "q");
    assert_eq!(full.answer, "a");

    let (input2, output2) = full.into_parts();
    assert_eq!(input2.question, "q");
    assert_eq!(output2.answer, "a");
}

#[test]
fn test_baml_type_impl() {
    // BamlType should be implemented
    let _ = <TestSig as BamlType>::baml_output_format();
}
```

## Compile-Time Error Tests

